cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.IT

This paper deals with computational learning theory, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses cryptographic assumptions, which falls under the scope of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of average case complexity suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper mentions a generalization of Feige's assumption, which is related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category as well.
